article.headline: Norfolk State 78, Towson 49
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Calvin Brown and Keith Young each scored 15 points to lead Norfolk State to a 78-49 win over Towson Wednesday night. Both teams started off slow, scoring 3 points each in the first 4 minutes. The Spartans (1-4) took the lead for good off Karandick Ogunride's layup with 13:48 left in the first half. That sparked a 14-2 run, capped off by a three-point play by Tony Murphy that put the Spartans up 19-7. Towson (2-2) fought back to bring it to within six at 22-16 with 5:54 left before the break, but Norfolk State took a 34-23 haltime lead. The Tigers again brought it to within six at 39-33 with 13:28 remaining, but Norfolk State pulled ahead, helped by a 25-5 run that put the Spartans up 73-44 with 2:12 left to play. Tony Murphy added 12 points and eight rebounds for the Spartans. Norfolk State had a school-record 20 steals, aided by four from Tynell Dunkley. Tim Crossin led Towson with 12 points, all 3-pointers.
